"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-02-paris-2024-olympics-enekwechi-advances-to-mens-shot-put-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Nigeria's Chukwuebuka Enekwechi has made it to the final of the men's shot put event at the 2024 Olympic Games, DAILY POST reports.  Enekwechi advanced into Saturday's final, placing fifth overall in qualification Group B.  The 31-year-old threw a distance of 21.13m to earn himself a place in the final.  The African champion is the first Nigerian to make it to the final of any event at the ongoing games.  It would be recalled that Enekwechi made it to the final of the shot put event four years ago in Tokyo.  He would be hoping to make it to the podium by finishing in the top three.  Three NPFL clubs jostle for Ernest's signature  Edo Queens sign 14 new players for CAF Women's Champions League qualifier  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"